Six years ago today…Maddy crossed over the rainbow bridge…she was a senior that came into my life shortly after I had lost Sebastian ( one of my very first pups) . Though Maddy and I only had less than 2 years together, she will always have a special place in my heart and soul. You never get over loosing them, you just adjust and give that extra love to others in their memory.
Adopt Senior Dogs, give them the BONUS years they deserve and spoil them rotten
Today marks Aanother year without this little one, he taught me so much and now I give his brothers and sister the love I didn’t always know how to give him. Love you spaz.

I’ve always loved the water…I scuba dived for the first time years ago and loved the quiet of being under water, the stillness. Sometimes wish I could stay under water forever. This was just for fun, I never do those things anymore. #justforfun #meditation

Reminder to self: Just Fu*king DO IT!  Stop second guessing and talking yourself out of going for the things you want. Trust that what is meant for you will come to you. 
So grateful for where I am in my life and grateful to the friends who have helped me get myself together again.  Photo: @dottavio77
Denim Jacket and Jeans is always my go-to…Classics never go out of style. Thank you @dottavio77 for some great photos.
Happy Labor Day….what was your highlight?

I’ve dealt with addiction for many years, there are many ways I’ve hurt myself and others, the worst one was that I gave up on myself and my life.

I’m so grateful to be working through this and here is something that has made a difference, I hope it helps you if you are dealing with the same thing.

1. keep your word to yourself.
2. Do the things you say you are going to do no matter what, or how hard they are, or if you just don’t feel feel like doing them.
3. Consistency, it’s one day at a time, one step at a time.
4. Don’t give up before the miracle happens, we don’t always know how close we are to the breakthrough.

This has been tremendously helpful to me and it’s taken me a long time to truly work this, I am forever grateful to Jason and Wes for your help, love and guidance.

Change is Good…
One thing I wish I had understood sooner is that  It’s ok to outgrow an old version of yourself, your friendships, wants, goals and desires…It opens the door to create who you want to be now.

Reminder to myself: Embrace change, embrace benign uncomfortable. 

Hope this helps someone today.

Feeling grateful today…Life IS good. Don’t know who needs to hear this…but something I have been practicing is: Forgiveness.  Forgiveness of self…”I forgive you” is something I keep reminding myself….for whatever thought comes into my head of 
“not being enough (fill in the blank)”
 I FORGIVE YOU….
It helps! But like anything in life, it’s a practice.

Wanted to post this as a reminder to myself….This was my very first “Professional” job. After hearing “No” or worst…hearing nothing at all from casting after auditioning. This was the 1 “Yes” that changed my life. I have been  @sagaftra member since 1998 and I can’t imagine what my career would have been without this Union behind me.
I say this as “a reminder” because I am again starting over, just a tad bit older and the industry has changed so much, I know hearing “NO” is a part of the game, but like anything In life that is worth it, I keep trying and keep getting up and taking the next step forward.
Don’t give up before the miracle happens.  @gap  BRING BACK THE ICONS! CLASSICS NEVER GO OUT OF STYLE.
